"""It is common for images of a countryâ€™s previous leaders, or other individuals of historical significance, 
to appear on its money. The individuals that appear on banknotes
in the United States are listed in the table below.
Write a program that begins by reading the denomination of a banknote from the
user. Then your program should display the name of the individual that appears on the
banknote of the entered amount. An appropriate error message should be displayed
if no such note exists.

Individual          Amount
George Washington     $1
Thomas Jefferson      $2
Abraham Lincoln       $5
Alexander Hamilton    $10
Andrew Jackson        $20
Ulysses S. Grant      $50
Benjamin Franklin     $100
"""
banknote = int(input("Please, introduce the value of your banknote: "))
if banknote == 1:
	print("The individual in the banknote is George Washington")
elif banknote == 2:
	print("The individual in the banknote is Thomas Jefferson")
elif banknote == 5:
	print("The individual in the banknote is Abraham Lincoln")
elif banknote == 10:
	print("The individual in the banknote is Alexander Hamilton")
elif banknote == 20:
	print("The individual in the banknote is Andrew Jackson")
elif banknote == 50:
	print("The individual in the banknote is Ulysses S. Grant")
elif banknote == 100:
	print("The individual in the banknote is Benjamin Franklin")
else:
	print("The value for the banknote is incorrect. ")
